{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPasswordInput"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudspasswordinput"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@","kind":"attribute"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSPasswordInput","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Layout","anchor":"Layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Passwords input is based on several configurable UI elements:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"label"}]},{"type":"text","text":": It is used to describe the purpose of the input."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"placeholder"}]},{"type":"text","text":":  A prefix is not common and is discouraged in a Password Input component. In very specific cases, it can provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"context or format requirements (e.g., “DEV-” for test accounts, “admin-” as a pattern to define an admin password)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lock icon"}]},{"type":"text","text":": it helps to reinforce the security context."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper text"}]},{"type":"text","text":":  A supporting text conveys additional information about the password field."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Outlined style","anchor":"Outlined-style"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"text":", the input is with a subtle background fill and invisible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["   \/\/ An outlined text input","   OUDSPasswordInput(label: \"Your password\", password: $password, isOutlined: true)","","   \/\/ With a localizable from a bundle","   OUDSPasswordInput(LocalizedStringKey(\"password_label\"), bundle: Bundle.module, password: $password)"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Rounded layout","anchor":"Rounded-layout"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As the","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":" OUDSTextInput"},{"text":", rounded corners can be enabled or disabled using the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hasRoundedTextInputs"},{"text":" values of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Tuning"},{"text":" object","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in your theme configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Status","anchor":"Status"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSPasswordInput"},{"text":" is based on the","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":" OUDSTextInput"},{"text":", all the status are the same and have the same behavior available here ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSTextInput.Status"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default no haptics are done by the component for the trailing action.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However you should think about cases wher you will have to make the devices vibrates.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can refer to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/design\/human-interface-guidelines\/playing-haptics","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Rich text","anchor":"Rich-text"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rich text can be used for error and helper texts.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Strong text can be used sparingly to highlight key information within the content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"No other text styles should be used.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Underlined text must not be applied manually (e.g. in error message), as it is commonly associated with hyperlinks and may mislead users.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Code samples","anchor":"Code-samples"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The password to display and edit","    @State var password: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ A basic password input with label","    OUDSPasswordInput(label: \"Password\", password: $password)","","    \/\/ Add a leading icon and helper text to more context","    OUDSPasswordInput(label: \"Password\", password: $password, lockIcon: true, helperText: \"Your password must be between 8 and 20 characters long.\")","","    \/\/ Password with prefix","    OUDSPasswordInput(label: \"Password\", password: $password, prefix: \"CORP-\")","","    \/\/ Make password visible","    OUDSPasswordInput(label: \"Password\", password: $password, isHiddenPassword: .constant(false))"]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation","anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-password-input","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering","anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"tex